Description: Wall sherd of East Greek, possibly Aeolian, grey ware pottery closed vessel, probably an oinochoe; exterior: worn dark grey slip and decoration in relief consisting of pendant palmette and tendrils.
Curator's comments: The sherd is from a vase closely similar to British Museum 1888,0601.644.f. The fabric and decorative techinques find parallels with British Museum 1888,0601.644.c. This sherd was analysed with NAA by Hans Mommsen (Bonn). The origin of the fabric (NAUK 47) was not identified and considered a chemical single.
Bibliographic references: Möller 2000 / Naukratis, Trade in Archaic Greece (p.259, no.4)
Johnston 1978 / Pottery from Naukratis: An Exhibition on the Occasion of the 11th International Congress of Classical Archaeology (no. 42)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GL.149)
